The paper deals with label shift estimation, which is a problem in machine learning. The paper discusses two dominant approaches for estimating the label marginal and presents a theoretical characterization of the likelihood-based estimator. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), computer vision (cs.CV), statistics (cs.STAT), and data structures and algorithms (cs.DS).
